results.name: Moebius transform of A129502.
link: Andrew Howroyd, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1024
formula: Dirichlet convolution of A209635 and A209229.
mathematica: a[n_] := Module[{e}, Sum[e = IntegerExponent[d, 2]; If[d == 2^e, MoebiusMu[n/d] Binomial[2 + e, 2], 0], {d, Divisors[n]}]];
a /@ Range[1, 100] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Sep 24 2019, from PARI *)
program: (PARI) a(n)={sumdiv(n, d,  my(e=valuation(d, 2)); if(d==1<<e, moebius(n/d) * binomial(2+e,2), 0))}
xref: Cf. A129502, A209229, A209635 (Moebius transform of A104117).
